Abdominal aortic aneurysm in the Irish population: a familial screening study. A pilot screening programme was undertaken in Ireland to determine the incidence of abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) (diameter 3 cm or greater) in the siblings of 120 patients known to have AAA. There were 621 siblings 270 of them were dead, 32 were over 80 years old and 85 lived outside Ireland, leaving 234 under 80 years of age still living in Ireland who were invited to attend for ultrasonographic screening. Of the 270 siblings who had died, 102 were women and 168 men